modules.description: This module provides functions to compress and decompress string data using the Deflate or Gzip algorithms. It supports streaming decompression and direct output to files, making it suitable for handling HTTP response bodies efficiently. Concrete use cases include processing compressed API responses and writing decompressed content directly to disk.

This module handles HTTP response decompression and header manipulation. It provides `decompress` to process compressed HTTP bodies using the content-encoding header, and `update_header` to manage accept-encoding headers for compression negotiation. Use it when consuming or modifying HTTP responses that may use gzip or deflate compression.

This module provides a configuration value that integrates with `ptime` for time-related functionality, specifically designed for use with `js_of_ocaml` via the `ptime.clock.js` binding. It works with the `unit Gz.Higher.configuration` type to define a concrete runtime configuration. A typical use case is setting up a time-aware configuration in a JavaScript environment using OCaml compiled to JavaScript.
